    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the clinical utility of triage screening for
      anemia and COP in the ED setting.This is a prospective, nonrandomized, multi-center study of
      the performance of simultaneous non-invasive testing for two common disorders (COP and
      anemia). We will determine the limits of agreement and performance characteristics of
      non-invasive SpCO and SpHb values compared to standard blood tests for measurement of COHb
      and hemoglobin, in the emergency department setting.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
